      "claimType": "workflow.critique.review",
      "fieldOrBehavior": "Claim.surface -> Claim.facet migration reviewed: 26 files migrated (production code, kit adapter test, and eval/fixture bundles), @kontourai/surface bumped to ^2.0.0, schemaVersion literals bumped to 5 wherever flow-agents constructs a bundle. One deliberate exception (kits/veritas-governance/adapter/readiness-to-trust-bundle.mjs) stays on the legacy surface/schemaVersion-3 shape and is clearly labeled, because its output is validated by @kontourai/flow's vendored hachure@0.5.1 schema (enum [2,3,4], surface required), which has not shipped the facet-rename bump yet -- confirmed by a real test failure (test_veritas_governance_kit.sh) when the migration was first attempted there, then reverted with an explanatory comment. Full CI baseline (evals/ci/run-baseline.sh, all 3 lanes, 37 checks) passes clean; unit tests 35/35 pass; build compiles cleanly; node scripts/ci/trust-reconcile.js --bundle delivery/trust.bundle reconciles all 32 required-lane manifest checks against fresh CI re-runs with zero divergences.",
      "value": "pass",
